h3. The do/while Loop 

* The do/while statement executes a block of statements repeatedly until a condition becomes false.
* Due to its structure, this loop necessarily executes the statements in the body of the loop at least once before testing its expression, which is found at the bottom of the block.
* The following examples demonstrate how the do/while loop works.
do
  { statements;}
while (condition);
